This paper is about machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of neural machine translation (NMT) models and the nmtpy framework suggest that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the use of attention mechanisms and ensembling techniques suggest that this paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The fact that the paper focuses on improving translation quality through back-translation suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), which often use similar techniques for data augmentation and improving model performance.
